cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.PL, cs.CE

The paper focuses on the study of cognitive activities in software development, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The involvement of cognitive psychologists and the use of a standard approach in cognitive science suggest that the paper may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of statistical analysis and the introduction of a formal hierarchical coding scheme suggest that the paper may also belong to the cybernetics (cs.CY) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on deriving lines of conduct or good practices suggests that the paper may also belong to the computer education (cs.CE) sub-category.
